Introduction - 
This project is about digital literacy, which is very important for students today. Almost everything we do now is connected to the internet, whether it is studying, submitting assignments, or communicating with others. Because of this, it becomes necessary to know how to use digital tools in the right and safe way.
In this project, I worked on five different tasks. Each task helped me learn something new, like creating designs, building a digital profile, using online platforms, writing emails, and understanding cyber safety. These tasks were not only useful for learning but also helped me understand how these things are used in real life. Overall, this project helped me become more aware and confident while using digital platforms.
Task 1 :-
For the first task, I created a digital literacy infographic using Canva. I chose Canva because it is easy to use and has many ready-made templates, which made my work simple. I did not have much experience in designing before, so this tool really helped me.
In my infographic, I included basic topics like what digital literacy is, some useful tools for students, safe internet practices, and how to maintain a good online presence. I tried to keep everything simple so that anyone can understand it without confusion. I used short points and some icons to make it look clean and interesting.
At the beginning, I faced a small problem because I had too much information and less space on one page. It looked a bit messy at first. But after trying a few different layouts, I was able to organize it properly. This task was actually enjoyable and helped me learn how to present information in a better way.
 Task 2 -
In Task 2, I created my digital portfolio using platforms like GitHub, LinkedIn, and HackerRank. Before this, I was not very familiar with these platforms, but while working on this task, I understood their importance.
GitHub is useful for storing and showing projects, LinkedIn helps in creating a professional profile, and HackerRank is used for practicing coding problems. I created my profiles and added basic details like my education and interests. I also tried solving a simple problem on HackerRank, which was a new experience for me.
This task made me realize that having an online presence is very important from the start of college. In the future, I will keep updating these platforms by adding my work and improving my skills. I think this will help me a lot when I apply for internships or jobs.
Task 3 :-
For Task 3, I worked on HackerRank and Google Forms. On HackerRank, I solved a beginner-level problem called “Solve Me First.” Even though it was simple, it helped me understand how coding platforms actually work. It was my first time solving a problem on such a platform, so it felt interesting.
I also created a Google Form with five questions related to digital literacy. The questions were simple and focused on topics like online safety, passwords, and basic awareness. This form can be used to test how much students know about digital safety.
This task was quite interesting because I learned two different things at the same time. One was coding practice, and the other was creating a form for collecting responses. These tools will definitely help me in my studies and make my work easier in the future.

Task 4 – 
Task 4 was about communication and email writing. In this task, I wrote two formal emails and created a checklist for social media use. Before this, I did not pay much attention to how emails should be written properly.
I learned that a good email should be simple, polite, and clear. It should have a proper subject line, greeting, and ending. If emails are not written properly, they can create confusion or leave a bad impression.
The checklist part helped me understand how to behave responsibly on social media. It reminded me that what we post online matters. This task improved my communication skills and made me more careful while writing messages.
Task 5 – 
In Task 5, I learned about phishing, which is a common type of cybercrime. I was actually surprised to see how easily people can get tricked by fake messages or websites that look very real.
This task made me realize that we often trust messages without thinking much, which can be risky. Even a small mistake, like clicking on a wrong link, can cause serious problems like losing money or personal data.
After doing this task, I will be more careful while using the internet. I will always check before clicking on any link and avoid sharing personal information with unknown sources. This task helped me become more aware about online safety.
CONCLUSION – 
This project helped me learn many useful things about digital literacy. I understood how to use different platforms, create content, and communicate in a better way. I also learned about online safety and how to protect myself from cyber threats.
All the tasks were practical and useful. They helped me improve my skills and made me more confident while using digital tools. I believe these learnings will help me in my academic journey and also in my future career. Overall, this project was a very good learning experience for me.
